- Cumulative statistics are calculated by summing up the player's statistics from the start of their career up to the current season;
- The query provides a detailed breakdown of player performance over time, allowing for the analysis of individual player growth and consistency;
- The results are ordered by player name and season ID, making it easier to track a player's progress over multiple seasons.

- The Premier League is a professional football league in England;
- The 2016/2017 season refers to the football season that started in August 2016 and ended in May 2017;
- Cumulative metrics are calculated by summing the respective statistics (goals for, goals against, wins) in the order of the teams' points, from the highest to the lowest.

- 'Triumphs' refers to the number of matches won;
- 'Stalemates' refers to the number of matches drawn;
- 'Defeats' refers to the number of matches lost;
- 'Goals scored' refers to the total number of goals the team scored in the season;
- 'Goals conceded' refers to the total number of goals the team allowed the opposition to score in the season;
- 'Points accumulated' refers to the total points the team earned in the season;
- 'Number of seasons played' refers to the count of seasons the team participated in.

- "More than just a small circle" refers to leagues with more than 18 teams;
- "Recent years" refers to seasons starting after 2010;
- "Stood tall but also outshone their peers" refers to teams that have more than 25 wins in a season.

- "Top players" refers to players ranked in the top 5 based on the number of goals scored;
- "Top teams" refers to teams ranked in the top 5 based on the total points earned;
- "Key performance metrics" include total appearances, goals, assists, yellow cards, red cards, minutes played, and shots on target for players; and total points, wins, draws, losses, goals for, goals against, and goal difference for teams.

- 'Premier League' is a top-tier English football league;
- '2015 to 2019' refers to the seasons starting from the year 2015 to the year 2019;
- 'average goals' refers to the mean number of goals scored per season.

- 'Shining stars' refers to the top 5 players;
- 'Lit up the court' means made the most assists;
- 'Latest season' is the most recent season based on the start year.

- "Titans of victory" refers to teams with the highest number of wins;
- "First season" refers to the season with `season_id = 1`;
- "Accolades" include the number of wins and total points earned.

- "Top scorers" refers to the players with the highest number of goals scored;
- "Leagues" are the top-level divisions in which teams compete;
- "Teams" are the groups of players that compete in the leagues.
